Finding User Account Information from the Command Line

Determine What Groups sysuser Belongs To
List the current working directory.
pwd
Run the following command:
id sysuser
Note the groups values returned in the output.

Determine sysusr’s Home Directory
Run the following command:
getent passwd sysuser
Note the user's home directory returned in the output.

Determine sysusr’s Login Shell
Run the following command:
cat /etc/passwd | grep sysuser
Note the login shell returned in the output.
Conclusion
